Q2. Assess Effectiveness & Document Lessons Learned (15 Marks)
Effectiveness Assessment
What Went Well	What Went Wrong
Quick containment stopped spread	No backup of file server (had to rebuild)
EDR alerts helped detection	Employee clicked phishing link despite training
Backup restored file server	2 hours downtime caused business impact
Lessons Learned Document
Incident Summary:

Ransomware via phishing email

1 workstation + file server affected

Resolved in 4 hours

Root Cause:

Employee opened malicious attachment from spoofed vendor email

What We Learned:

Backups are critical – We will implement daily automated backups

Email filtering needs improvement – Will add sandboxing for attachments

User training must be repeated – Quarterly phishing simulations

Containment was fast – Will maintain same response speed

